This paper deals with analyzing web logs to understand human behavior, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as preferential linking and queuing, which are relevant to the fields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and system dynamics (cs.SD). The study also involves analyzing user navigation patterns, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
